The paper focuses on creating and analyzing symmetry and symmetry breaking in digital art, which involves computer graphics and computer vision techniques. Therefore, cs.GR (Graphics) and cs.CV (Computer Vision) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also mentions the use of algorithms and computational aesthetic measures, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.MM (Multimedia) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper discusses the analysis of design parameters, which could be related to machine learning and optimization, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) a possible sub-category as well.
